text: Only the best people! @realdonaldtrump: In 2010, Tuberville was a co-defendant with John David Stroud in a lawsuit brought against TS Capital LLC, which the two had founded. The lawsuit was filed by investors and alleged that Tuberville and Stroud co-managed a hedge fund that

defrauded investors of $1.7 million. In October 2011, the Business Conduct Committee of the National Futures Association, a self-regulating industry organization, took "emergency enforcement action" to permanently bar the firm from soliciting, accepting, transferring

or disbursing any funds from investors . Stroud was found guilty in August 2013 of securities fraud, ordered to pay $2.1 million in restitution and serve 10 years in jail. The case against Tuberville was settled on October 10, 2013, but terms were not disclosed.
Perhaps Stroud should replace Clayton as SEC commissioner? Drain the Swamp, Donald? Give us a break... @jimcramer @tomkeene @riskreversal @ScottWapnerCNBC @threadreaderapp unroll
